<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870304-0064 </DOCNO><HL> Credit Ratings</HL><DD> 03/04/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> PCCBOND MARKET NEWS (BON) </IN><DATELINE> PUROLATOR COURIER CORP.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Standard andamp; Poor's Corp. said it placed ratings on the Basking Ridge, N.J.-based package delivery company's industrial revenue bonds on its CreditWatch list with negative implications. The bonds currently are rated double-B-plus. About $53 million of debt is affected. The rating concern cited the proposed $268 million leveraged buyout of the company by a group of officers and a unit of E.F. Hutton Group Inc. Sandamp;P, noting that the company's express courier business posted losses in 1985 and 1986, also said the package delivery business is becoming increasingly competitive. A Purolator official said the Sandamp;P move had been expected. </TEXT></DOC>